---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Project.astro";
import Heading from "@/components/ui/Heading.astro";
import Text from "@/components/ui/Text.astro";
import ProjectContnetWrapper from "@/components/ui/ProjectContnetWrapper.astro";
import SwiperSlider from "@/components/ui/SwiperSlider.astro";
import { loadImages } from "@/utils/loadImages";

import detail1Img from "@/assets/mtsDecor/1.png";
import detail2Img from "@/assets/mtsDecor/2.png";
import excelImg from "@/assets/mtsDecor/excel.png";
import planfactImg from "@/assets/mtsDecor/planfact.png";
import workflowImg from "@/assets/mtsDecor/workflow.png";
import logoImg from "@/assets/mtsDecor/logo.png";

const title = "MTS Digital";
const years = "2022-2023";
const description =
  "MTS - Russia's largest telecommunications company with 100M+ subscribers";

const imageModulesFirst = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/mts1/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif}"
);
const imageModulesSecond = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/mts2/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif}"
);
const imageModulesThird = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/mts3/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif}"
);

const sliderImagesFirst = await loadImages(imageModulesFirst);
const sliderImagesSecond = await loadImages(imageModulesSecond);
const sliderImagesThird = await loadImages(imageModulesThird);
---

<Layout {title} {years} {description} logo={logoImg}>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      Led the foundational design for MTS's first digital media planning
      platform, establishing core UX principles and user flows for enterprise
      media buyers. This greenfield B2B product aimed to transform traditional
      manual media planning processes into a streamlined digital experience.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Challenge</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      Media planning agencies were spending 2+ weeks manually creating media
      plans in Excel spreadsheets, coordinating across multiple channels (web,
      mobile, TV) without centralized workflow management. The market lacked a
      comprehensive solution for Russian media landscape.
    </Text>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      At first the whole project looked like a small task: take a huge Excel
      spreadsheet and turn it into a web format.
    </Text>
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <Image
    src={excelImg}
    alt="The original media plan template in Excel"
    width="657"
    densities={[1, 2]}
    class="m-auto mb-[25px]"
  />
  <Text class="mb-[50px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    The starting point: the media plan template in Excel. 99 columns and 242
    rows.
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">My Role</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[60px]">
      As lead designer, I built the platform design from scratch and owned the
      entire process from research through MVP delivery, working directly with
      product management and engineering teams.</Text
    >
    <Heading
      class="mt-[100px] mb-[10px] text-[28px]"
      level={2}
      weight="semibold">Design Strategy</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[25px]"
      >Working on a 0-to-1 enterprise product, I prioritized core functionality
      over feature breadth, focusing on complex user workflows through direct
      stakeholder research.</Text
    >

    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Research & Discovery</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      I ran interviews with media planners inside the company, and we kept
      weekly sessions with them through the whole project. Because of an NDA I
      was not allowed to talk to planners from other companies.
    </Text>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      These calls showed that the task was much bigger than moving a table to
      the web: plans go through approvals at different stages, planners wanted
      to launch internet ads right from the platform, and they wanted to see
      analytics in the same place. The interviews also revealed two key user
      groups: primary planners managing end-to-end campaigns, and collaborative
      teams requiring approval workflows with version control constraints.
    </Text>

    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold"
      >Product Strategy Decision</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[25px]">
      Given that clients were already using Excel-based workflows, we chose an
      MLP approach over basic MVP to reduce migration friction and deliver
      immediate value.
    </Text>
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <Image
    src={detail1Img}
    alt="detail1Img"
    width="657"
    class="m-auto mb-[50px]"
  />
  <Text class="mb-[40px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    I used the MLP framework to balance essential functionality with user
    delight, ensuring competitive advantage over existing Excel workflows.
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">UI Design</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[60px]"
      >After the initial stages, I consistently conducted interviews with
      potential users. As a result, over the course of a year, the product was
      nearly fully designed, with the primary user flow comprising approximately
      60 frames and an additional 300 frames for various states.</Text
    >
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <Image
    src={workflowImg}
    alt="The final version of the platform workflow scheme"
    width="657"
    densities={[1, 2]}
    class="m-auto mb-[25px]"
  />
  <Text class="mb-[50px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    The final version of the platform workflow scheme.
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Image
      src={detail2Img}
      alt="detail2Img"
      width="556"
      class="m-auto mb-[100px]"
    />
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <div class="mb-[25px]">
    <SwiperSlider sliderImages={sliderImagesFirst} initialWidth="270px" />
  </div>
  <Text class="mb-[100px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    Campaign Approval Workflow
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Plan vs Fact</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      Another stage we brought into the platform is the plan-fact report. You
      plan one thing and get another, so planners tracked the difference in a
      separate Excel report with 286 columns. In the platform this became a
      report with detailed analytics.
    </Text>
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <Image
    src={planfactImg}
    alt="The original plan-fact report in Excel"
    width="657"
    densities={[1, 2]}
    class="m-auto mb-[25px]"
  />
  <Text class="mb-[50px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    The plan-fact report in Excel. 286 columns.
  </Text>
  <div class="mt-[100px] mb-[25px]">
    <SwiperSlider sliderImages={sliderImagesSecond} initialWidth="275px" />
  </div>
  <Text class="mb-[100px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    Flexible Analytics Configuration.<br />Advanced dashboard builder allowing
    media planners to customize their workspace. Users can select from multiple
    chart types (line graphs, bar charts, pie charts, spreadsheets) and
    configure data sources to match their specific reporting needs.
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">From Digital to TV</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[60px]">
      Once all of this worked for internet advertising, we asked: why not do
      the same for TV? Nothing like that existed in Russia at that time. With
      the team we built TV ad planning with the option to pick and buy a
      specific ad block, plus the same flexible automatic budget distribution
      as for internet ads.
    </Text>
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <div class="mb-[50px]">
    <SwiperSlider sliderImages={sliderImagesThird} initialWidth="275px" />
  </div>
  <Text class="mb-[100px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    Television Media Slot Management.<br />Complex TV scheduling interface
    enabling precise time slot selection across multiple channels and programs.
    The grid-based system shows real-time availability, pricing, and audience
    demographics, allowing planners to optimize reach and frequency for
    broadcast campaigns.
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Outcome</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[50px]">
      We shipped the platform to production inside the corporation, with a plan
      to sell it to other corporations and marketing agencies.
    </Text>
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
</Layout>
